{
  "doc_id": "12060",
  "text": "It is well known that supplying gain to plasmonic nanostructures can compensate for SPP dissipation caused by Ohmic losses and other damping mechanisms [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . To suppress the damping of SPPs in a metallic nanoparticle chain, recent works have considered embedding nanoparticles into active media [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] or putting gain materials inside metallic shells [CITATION_7] . Since these are the two basically different ways to overcome material losses in the system, it is important to compare them in terms of their efficiency to compensate for losses.",
